I then focused on the province resolution (60-NQ/TW).  It confirms that Hưng Yên *remains* Hưng Yên, even after merging with Thái Bình.  No major changes there.

Next, I delved into the more complex 1666/NQ-UBTVQH15 resolution.  I carefully scanned the lines, specifically looking for "Đông Kết."  Line 18 jumped out: it explicitly stated that "Xã Đông Kết" was being merged with other units to form the new "Xã Khoái Châu."  The other lines didn't contain any relevance to this.

I then consulted the "New wards" dataset and found a perfect match for "Xã Khoái Châu,"  including its ward code (12205) and province information.

Based on this direct mapping, my confidence is *high* that this is the correct translation. I constructed the JSON output accordingly, citing the specific resolution line (18) as evidence.  I have ensured that I considered the original request for *all* possible candidates; however, in this case, the resolution provided a clear and singular outcome.
